I analyzed the environmental strategies of global fashion brands by text-mining their ESG reports. The pipeline executed text preprocessing, TF-IDF, LDA (Latent Dirichlet Allocation), and semantic network analysis.
The study concluded that brands with stronger climate-responsive strategies exhibit higher emotional stability and strategic consistency in their ESG management. This work received the Best Student Paper Award at the conference.
